1 packet Creamy Pesto Dressing
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
200 g Pulled Pork
1 packet Leek
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Deluxe Salad Mix
1 Carrot
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Tomato Paste
white wine vinegar
g butter
water
1 drizzle olive oil

• Preheat grill to medium-high heat.
• Grate carrot.
Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook carrot and sliced leek until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add All-American spice blend, tomato paste and pulled pork. Cook, breaking up with a spoon, until warmed through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then stir through the butter and water until combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

• Drizzle a baking dish with olive oil. Lay a mini flourtortilla on a flat surface. Spoon pork mixture down the centre. Roll tortilla up tightly and place, seam-side down, in the baking dish.
• Repeat with remaining tortillas and pork mixture, ensuring they fit together snugly in the baking dish. Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Grill enchiladas until cheese is melted and golden and tortillas are warmed through, 8-10 minutes.
Little cooks: Take charge of assembling the enchiladas!

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine deluxe salad mix, creamy pesto dressing and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to taste.
• Divide pulled pork enchiladas between plates.
• Serve with creamy pesto salad. Enjoy!